{"questionId":"13919445","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Felix uses the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> shown in part (b) to estimate the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The gradient is estimated to be&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>672</mn></math>&nbsp;when&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math>.&nbsp;Taking <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>g</mi></math> to be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>, use this information to show that Felix found that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>672</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1600</mn><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct left-hand side and <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for correct right-hand side.</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>672</mn></mrow><mn>1600</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1A0</strong> </em>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math> substituted into the right-hand side of the&nbsp;expression, leading to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>672</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13919445","referenceCode":"23N.3.AHL.TZ0.1cii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"The gradient is estimated to be 9.672 when v=40. Taking g to be 9.8, use this information to show that Felix found that k=8×10-5.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.11—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.14—Setting up a DE, solve by separating variables","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}